text: The 1833 Morpeth by-election was held on 31 December 1833 It was won by the unopposed Whig candidate Edward George Granville Howard who replaced his brother Frederick George Howard. ==References== Category:By-elections to the Parliament of the United Kingdom in Northumberland constituencies Category:Unopposed by-elections to the Parliament of the United Kingdom in English constituencies Category:1833 in England Category:1833 elections in Europe Category:19th century in Northumberland Category:Morpeth, Northumberland Category:December 1833 events
title: 1833 Morpeth by-election
